LEE RESEARCH GROUP @ UTK HOME (current) RESEARCH PUBLICATIONS MEMBERS NEWS CONTACT WELCOME TO LEE RESEARCH GROUP! Department of Physics and Astronomy, University of Tennessee, Knoxville We are exploring novel physical phenomena 
			by studying electronic, magnetic, and superconducting behaviors in (topological) quantum materials as well as potential quantum device applications in quantum computing and spintronics! Experimental schemes of molecular beam epitaxy ; 
			structural, electronical, and magnetic characterizations ; 
			fabrication of mesoscopic and nanoscale devices ; 
			electrical transport using cryostats are used for our research. Selected Research Topics are listed below. Details can be found in the "RESEARCH" page. Epitaxy of Quantum Materials Quantum Transport Topological Quantum Computing [Openings] We are currently recruiting graduate and undergraduate students.
	  If you are interested in quantum materials, nano-scale devices, and quantum transport as well as applications of quantum materials,
	      contact us! LEE RESEARCH GROUP 401 Nielsen Bldg • 1408 Circle Drive • Knoxville TN 37996 Phone: (865) 974-8705 • Email: jslee@utk.edu
